    "Secondly, it extracts essential features and reduces redundant information, thereby improving the model's generalization ability and interpretability.",
    "The max pooling operation selects the maximum value within each region as the output, thereby ignoring the information of other values.",
    "This may lead to the neglect or loss of some critical features, especially in cases involving small-sized features.",
    "This information loss can affect the model's perception of details.",
    "Max pooling preserves the maximum value of the input, but it loses the positional information of that maximum value in the feature map."
